Citation.sTitle: Vapor Liquid Equilibrium for Several Compounds Relevant to the Biofuels Industry Modeled with the Wilson Equation
Citation.sAbstract: Vapor-liquid equilibrium measurements have been performed on several binary systems incorporating chemicals of interest to the biofuels industry. Systems were chosen based on two criteria: (1) similarity to measurement requests received by Wiltec and (2) suitability of using the Wilson Equation to model the activity coefficients for the VLE data. The Wilson Equation is a good choice for modeling fully miscible solutions of moderately polar compounds. With these two ideas in mind, systems were chosen incorporating the following compounds: 1-methoxy-2- propanol (MOPO), 2-furaldehyde (FUR), allyl alcohol (AllOH), butyl acetate (BACE), carbon dioxide (CO2), carbon disulfide (CS2), carbonyl sulfide (COS), ethanolamine (EOA), ethyl acetate (EACE), n-butanol (nBOH), pentane (PEN), and t-butanol (tBOH). Measurement temperatures ranged from -25 to +200deg C.
